Class TermEntry

java.lang.Object
  plugins.ccuration.index.TermEntry
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
TermFileEntry, TermPageEntry
public abstract class TermEntry
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<TermEntry>

Represents data associated with a given subject String term. Subclasses '''must''' override the following methods to use information specific to that subclass: * entryType() * compareTo(TermEntry) * equals(Object) * hashCode()

entryType

public abstract TermEntry.EntryType entryType()
Returns the type of TermEntry. This '''must''' be constant for instances of the same class, and different between classes.

compareTo

public int compareTo(TermEntry o)
Compares two entries, based on how useful they might be to the end user. This implementation sorts by order of descending relevance, then by order of ascending entryType(). Subclasses '''must overridde this method'' to also use information specific to the subclass.

Specified by:
compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<TermEntry>
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the entries have different subjects

equals

public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
This implementation tests whether the run-time classes of the argument is identical to the run-time class of this object. If they are, then it tests the relevance and subject fields. Subclasses '''must overridde this method'' to also use information specific to the subclass.
